In recent years, it is found that bicarbonate (HCO3−) can not only react with H2O2 to form HCO4− with high reactivity but also act as an auxiliary for water-oxidative H2O2 evolution under photoelectrochemical (PEC) condition, through a reversible reaction as follows8,9:1HCO3−+H2O2↔HCO4−+H2O\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
